Late to post 🤍🤍🤍 

A magical Christmas night. 

I spent last Christmas & winter away in another country. So this get together for the holidays meant so much to me. 

There is NO place like home for the holidays. 

Especially when your crew is this incredible. I love you all and I am beyond blessed to have your presence around me & supporting me. 

Unbelievable night for unbelievable souls 🤍✨

Her * - * .. you know her. 

The one who you feel within you in moments of depth, and dreaming up your incredible future. 
The one who picks you up when you’ve fallen, standing in integrity, understanding and poise. 
The one who calls to you daily, asking you to take that extra step to learn, feel, grow and succeed. 

She is the one who has been there within you, pushing you to do everything you have ever wanted. 

She is the one who is leading you from the most aligned place of your life - holding you at every step and reminding you of your purpose. 

She is the one who is everything you are already.

—- 
I am her. 
She is me. 

And.. it is perfect timing that I have now met her, and meet her daily. 
Because we have a lot of incredible things to do together in this life. 
—- 

She is calm, she is heart-centered, she is witty, she is extremely friendly, she is driven, she is respected and respects all, she is bold and beautiful, she is wild, she is inspiring, she is a leader, she is the boss, she is aligned with herself and her values, she is a philanthropist, she is connected to the ocean, she is obsessed with her goals, and she is the go-to for anyone looking to lead an extremely joyful and aligned life. And most importantly, she puts love first above everything else. 

This is my her. If you took time to write down everything about your her, or your him, what would it say?

#highestself #selfimage #self

Hey 👋🏼 I’m Lindsay 

You can call me a visionary, a creative, and deeply connected + caring woman. I’m Vice President of an amazing company called Riceworks, providing beautiful buildings for people to work in, live in and relax in. We also do many cool things in the finance world. Alongside this, I am passionate about a few things, including self development + alignment, racing cars ( I competed professionally for 5 years!) & the ocean. I currently offer selective personalized coaching (my heart!!!) and share my tools of how I stepped into a better mindset/better attitude on life, while being there FULLY to help beautiful souls feel into their alignment in life. I am also a former race car driver who owned her own race team here in Canada in my twenties - and I still enjoy getting behind the wheel in stunts for commercials and (safe) fun. And finally, I’ve always been drawn to the ocean - so one year ago I hopped into the water to learn freediving. This, along with saving the whales, and making a bigger impact on humans through all of my work, is what I dream of on my days at home on my farm with my pooch Drake. 

In the last year, I have stepped into higher levels of self responsibility, compassion for my heart & my body, and enjoyment of the moment. I checked off three bucket list items (I swam with a whale!!), and I got appointed to the board of @marinemegafauna in Canada. Wooooph 🌱🐳🙏🏼

I jump, I sing, I run, I play. I am unapologetic about who I am (that took me a little while), and I shower those that I love with abundant  love. I am also very natural-driven in my life for what I consume (food, health products, technology), allow into my space, and call into my life 🙏🏼🥰

Here you will find nuggets of love, insights on life, and positivity for your pleasure - and stories of me and what I am getting up to and what’s inspiring me. 

I truly enjoy my time OFF of social media so I am not super active in sharing daily insights, however if you ever message me directly for advice, questions, or support I most certainly will be there to answer 🤍✔️✨

Welcome, and I can’t wait to meet you 🤍

Lately - - just love. 

What if - instead of running or filling your mind or fearing life - you loved? 

Instead of asking yourself all of the reasons or ways things can turn out poorly - you stepped into it. You took the chance, led with your heart, and went for the things you fear, daringly. 

You went for the things that kicked you out of your comfort zone. The things that stretched you so much - so much - that in the end, you are only able to be in the moment. Day by day. 

Trekking through the unknown territory. Day by day.

Lately - - just love. My mantra my mood my muse for the rest of my life. 

How do I step more truly into my heart? 

I look at myself with awareness everyday. 

I look at how I can show up in a more meaningful way for all of those around me. 

How I can listen more, without needing to speak. How I can contribute in real ways, without needing to be rewarded for my ideas. How I can offer more gifts, by giving my time. 

I look at how I can create more joy in my heart daily. How I can have more fun and more meaning and PLAY. 

And - - it’s working. Life is changing. Priorities shift. And you come back to the simplicity of what’s the ONLY thing that matters through this all : LOVE. 

#justlove, people ✨

At the end of the day, I want to feel as if I really lived my life. 

As if I really deeply truly loved - and fully opened my heart to incredible people. 

As if I did the things that terrified me and put me way out of my own comfort zone. 

As if I pursued each and every moment that I knew would bring me joy + passion - without hesitation. 

As if I took each and every gift in my life and created impact with them that were always bigger than me. 

And - as if in every moment of my life I embraced being the powerful, imperfect me that I am 🤍✨

This year has brought me a lot of success, blessings and it has brought me closer to ‘her’. 

The ‘her’ that is fierce yet soft, smart yet unspoken, beautiful yet humble. 

When I step into these shoes (this way of being)- I become more trusting and aligned with the real (inspiring) me.

And for sure don’t forget to take every inch you can get when it means you get closer to what you deeply want.

3. Ego aside 🤍🙏🏼

You’ll be surprised what can come to you in this space ^.

Speechless and in love 🤍🥹

My PORSCHE 911 guys - this is a dream I’ve had for the longest time. A dream and a serious goal that I’ve been aiming for, for a very long time. 

I now have it 🥹 My raw power. My driver’s car. My short shifter gear box. My turbo engine. My 3.0L of love. My Porsche growl. My heart skip a beat moment that I now get to have every single day I want.

Its been an interesting time being out of a sports car for 2 years (in 2020 I stopped racing and in 2021 I sold my Golf R) - and this has been a patience tester for me. Waiting to get the one car that I really wanted. Even playing with ideas of getting back into a race car. 

All I know is for now, I’ll drive. Ill drive with that same smile on my face and a knowing that the pure joy I feel behind the wheel is now accessible through my very own Porsche key. 

And as for racing - the next time I see a turn off on the road that looks like fun, I’ll turn right and take it. We will only know then 😊✨

There’s no feeling like stepping on the pedal, shifting gears, and hearing your baby roar. 

Next stop @pfafftuning and @bestlineautotech to start making him mine 😛🙏🏼✨

#porsche911 #racer #ladydriven

It’s been a while since I have really shared myself online - and I feel I’ve been holding back. 

Sometimes I have wondered what I have to share - but you need you realize that there are people out there wanting and needing to hear your story or hear from you. 

I love sharing my life / life lessons with everyone that’s close to me.. so it’s time to bring some of that here. 

I also love watching beautiful videos, and I wanted to start making them myself and getting better at it. 

Something inside of me stopped me for a long time but here I am - I am stepping outside of that next comfort zone and putting myself out there ✨🤍 

I’ve reflected, and this is what I KNOW I can share with you :

✨ Toxin free foods and lifestyle
✨ Wellness and health choices
✨ What makes my life better 
✨ self improvement + self love
✨ my home, design, farm life
✨ race cars, racing, and doing stunts for media
✨ real estate investment (domestic or foreign)
✨ investing and financial life 
✨ property management
✨ all things my dog Drake 
✨ fashion + my style 
✨ travel content + my airbnbs

Ya, it’s a lot 😊 

WHAT DO YOU WANT TO HEAR FROM ME? ^^

I’d love your feedback and to understand what you’d love to learn. 
#newera #pushingboundaries #lindsayrice

Remember that there are people who weren’t given the blessings you were. 

Remember that there is a significant amount of people who may not have the basic necessities of life you’ve always had. 

Giving back and supporting those in need is an incredible thing to be able to do, and I’m really grateful to support an organization like this one. 

Their programs for youth ate unparalleled 🤯 with everything from cooking classes, to job resources, counselling, to soccer leagues and even a high school under their roof. Big thanks to @covenanthousetoronto for the tour and I am proud to support such a beautiful, heart warming space. A lot of their fund raising comes from private funding so keep this in mind the next time you’re able to give 🫶🏼

What an absolutely BRILLIANT year 🤍✨

This year :
I blew past spaces that held me back. 
I doubled my income.
I bought my DREAM CAR 🏎️ (Porsche 911)
I placed focus on my health (the most important thing)
I took amazing trips to Portland, Miami (F1), Cabo san Lucas, and Quintana Roo. 
I laughed harder with my friends. 
I got to know myself so deeply. 
I opened to a love I didn’t know I had in me♥️

The past 3 years have been a season of discovery for me. When we pass through our season of discovery, we come out the other side with a deeper knowing of what we want for ourselves and how we want our lives to feel. I know this so SO much now. 

One vision that i always have always held and reflected on daily is : HER. 

The version of me that is absolutely doing all of the things she wants. 

♥️ Making an empire that supports all of my dreams
♥️ Getting connected with her inner world everyday 
♥️ Being so BOLD and honest in life 
♥️ Finding smart ways to invest my money 
♥️ Saving enough money to support my lifestyle and my future goals 
♥️ Not apologizing for who I am - ever
♥️ Enjoying beautiful spaces in the world without a second guess
♥️ Loving the clothes, buying the clothes, wearing the clothes (no matter the price tag) 
♥️ Doing all the things I need to do to reach my goals 
♥️ DREAMING BIGGER 
♥️ Being the version of me that makes me smile in the mirror each and every day

They said 2023 was going to be the year - but for me I know its going to be 2024. 

#becomingher #boldandbeautiful #bigdreams #businesswoman

Everyday hits a little different. 

But we all know those days where everything feels right, just as it is. 

Our heart is open, our chin is up, and we are incredibly content with all the beauty that comes our way. 

Remember to bask in these moments, minutes, days. These are the ones to keep and hold so dear. 

A little more presence is what the world needs and what is so healing to whatever is going on with us at the moment. Even if it’s small. 

Productivity isn’t always the answer - rest does just as good. 

So rest into the incredible happiness that comes your way. 

#hitsdifferent #bestday #happiness #happinessquotes #inspirational
